</p>
{% endif %}

{# v0.23.0 — Section 5.6: Multi-Victim Cluster. When this case
   is bound to a multi-victim cluster (via shared perp wallets
   with prior cases), surface the cluster identifier + aggregated
   loss + co-victim count. This is the signal that says "this is
   not a one-off — coordinate the filing with the prior victims'
   AUSAs." Hidden when no cluster overlap. #}
{% if cluster_membership and cluster_membership.member_case_count and cluster_membership.member_case_count >= 2 %}
<h2>5.6 Multi-Victim Cluster</h2>
<div class="summary-box action">
  <p style="margin:0">
    <strong>This case is bound to cluster
    {{ cluster_membership.public_id }}.</strong>
    Aggregated across the cluster:
    <strong>{{ cluster_membership.member_case_count }}</strong>
    victim case{{ "s" if cluster_membership.member_case_count != 1 else "" }}
    with combined losses of
    <strong>{{ cluster_membership.total_loss_usd_human }}</strong>.
    This case shares perpetrator infrastructure with
    <strong>{{ cluster_membership.co_victim_count }}</strong>
    other Recupero-traced victim{{ "s" if cluster_membership.co_victim_count != 1 else "" }}.
  </p>
</div>
<p class="small">
  The binding wallet (the perpetrator-controlled address that
  appears across cases) is
  <span class="mono">{{ cluster_membership.joined_via_address }}</span>
  on {{ cluster_membership.joined_via_chain }}. Recupero detected
  this overlap at brief-render time by querying our cross-case
  address index against the perp wallets in this trace.
</p>
<h3>Recommended coordination</h3>
<ol>
  <li>
    Cross-reference cluster <strong>{{ cluster_membership.public_id }}</strong>
    with any open federal cases naming the binding wallet. Recupero
    can supply the complete cluster member list (case identifiers,
    AUSA contacts where on file, per-victim loss) on request.
  </li>
  <li>
    Consider whether a consolidated multi-victim filing is
    appropriate. Recupero's aggregated cluster handoff
    deliverable (rendered via
    <span class="mono">recupero-ops render-cluster {{ cluster_membership.public_id }}</span>)
    produces a single LE-handoff document covering every victim
    in the cluster.
  </li>
  <li>
    If the binding wallet has not yet been added to an
    enforcement watchlist, the consolidated cluster size
    (<strong>{{ cluster_membership.total_loss_usd_human }}</strong>
    aggregated loss) typically meets the threshold for OFAC
    designation review under 31 CFR § 583 or for inclusion in
    the FBI Cyber Division priority targets.
  </li>
</ol>
{% endif %}

{# v0.24.0 — Section 5.7: Per-Issuer Cooperation Profile. For each
   issuer in the freeze ask list, surface their cross-case
   cooperation history (response rate, median response hours,
   full_freeze_rate) + recommended legal instrument. Hidden when
   cooperation_profiles is empty (no DSN / no prior history). #}
{% if cooperation_profiles and cooperation_profiles.items() | list %}
<h2>5.7 Issuer Cooperation Profile</h2>
<p class="small">
  Cross-case cooperation history for each issuer named in the
  freeze ask list, aggregated from Recupero's full freeze-letter
  history. Each row shows whether informal freeze requests have
  historically produced results for this specific issuer, the median
  time to first response, and the recommended legal instrument given
  the cooperation profile + jurisdiction + sanctions exposure.
</p>
<table class="evidence">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Issuer</th>
      <th>Letters on file</th>
      <th>Response rate</th>
      <th>Median response</th>
      <th>Full freeze rate</th>
      <th>Recommended instrument</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    {% for issuer_name, prof in cooperation_profiles.items() %}
    <tr{% if prof.get('is_black_hole') %} style="background:#fef2f2"{% endif %}>
      <td><strong>{{ issuer_name }}</strong>
        {% if prof.get('is_black_hole') %}
